{
  "stem": "20616.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you know what's good for him, see to it that he doesn't do that anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And later I was invited by the City of Wiesbaden, by the way, two years ago.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That is-- I was asked whom I would like to see in Wiesbaden.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Ralph was the one person I wanted to see.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never had anything against him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I found out that he had-- did not want to see me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I tried a few times to try to get somebody-- the-- somebody who taught at the school and who was active in the city and who knew him, actually, to talk to him.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But he said, no, he doesn't want to see me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was told also that his father was quite a-- a Nazi.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But my father always said, no, he's not a Nazi.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he always was on very good terms with him and I was on very good terms with his son.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So sometimes you don't know people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I came back in January, 1946.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went back home again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went back to the firm where I worked before.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And business was very slow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of the diamond-cutting businesses went out-- went bankrupt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they stayed in business for I think a month or two and then they closed shop because the diamond industry was dead as far as New York is concerned.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It went to Palestine, to Puerto Rico for the less expensive stones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was some-- there was also a clique of-- of diamond dealers and cutters from Antwerp who stuck very closely together and got sort of-- got rid of all the-- the people who joined later who did not belong to that group.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
